---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const blogContent = `
<p><em>An overview of our update shifting Perqed from a formal verification wrapper into an autonomous hypothesis engine backed by native empirical validation.</em></p>

<h2>The Crucible: Intersecting Orthogonal Domains</h2>
<p>Our previous orchestrator (v2.0) excelled at confirming known combinatorial bounds via targeted simulated annealing. To move into generating unmapped mathematical conjectures, we implemented a cross-pollination mechanism.</p>

<p>Rather than running a linear literature search, the <code>IdeatorAgent</code> now queries a local LanceDB vector store to ingest a primary paper and intentionally pairs it with a structurally sound but conceptually distant domain. </p>

<p>In a recent execution probing maximal graph clique bounds, the system ingested a fractional matching paper and bridged it with a secondary retrieval on Hopf Algebras in Quantum Field Theory. By forcing the abstraction into orthogonal domains, the agent bypassed standard textbook replication and yielded a mathematically novel synthesis structure.</p>

<h2>The Falsification Loop: Enforcing Rigor</h2>
<p>LLMs natively struggle with empirical constraints and prefer hallucinating plausible logic over failing. We implemented a strict execution boundary to correct this.</p>

<ol>
<li><strong>Sandboxed Execution</strong>: The engine now writes and executes its probing scripts within a heavily isolated local Python environment pre-configured with <code>sympy</code>, <code>scipy</code>, <code>networkx</code>, and <code>z3-solver</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Automated Error Correction</strong>: When an agent's code fails due to syntax or strict dependency issues, the <code>ExplorerAgent</code> drops into a <code>try/catch</code> repair loop. It reads the local traceback and patches its own implementation before returning execution output.</li>
<li><strong>Selective Skill Injection</strong>: We mapped 38 specialized mathematical tools (from homological techniques to specific SMT encodings) to their relevant domains. A Domain Affinity Mapper now filters and injects only the necessary techniques into the context window, avoiding JSON truncation and keeping the execution tightly focused on the relevant algebra.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Empirical Rejection</h2>
<p>The engine is intentionally designed to falsify its own work. If a generated hypothesis contradicts the established transcendence of an even zeta value, the pipeline doesn't force a hallucinated formal proof. The Sympy script simply flags the counter-example in the empirical pass, and the system discards the hypothesis.</p>

<p>During a recent run analyzing Quandle colorings mapped to Torus knots, the engine correctly identified a combinatorial explosion in its test logic. Unwilling to assert an uncomputable result, the orchestrator analyzed its finite-field computations and yielded an unexpected integer-partition constraint as a clean, open Number Theory conjecture. </p>

<p>It fails fast, proves its failures empirically, and narrows the scope to what is actually solvable.</p>
`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Perqed v3.0: Autonomous Falsification and Interdisciplinary Synthesis — Perqed" activeNav="blog">

  <article class="article">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <header class="article-header">
          <div class="article-meta">
            <time>April 3, 2026</time>
            <span class="sep">·</span>
            <span>4 min read</span>
          </div>
          <h1>Perqed v3.0: Autonomous Falsification and Interdisciplinary Synthesis</h1>
        </header>

        <div set:html={blogContent} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article {
    padding: 64px 0 80px;
  }

  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .article-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .sep {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .article :global(blockquote) {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 16px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
